    "recap_headline": "Baseball",
    "recap_text": "LOS ANGELES\n\u2013 The No. 12 USC baseball team kept its perfect record intact with a 7-6 walkoff victory in the 10\nth\ninning against San Diego on Wednesday night at Dedeaux Field.\nAdrian Lopez\nhit a sacrifice fly to center, scoring\nLogan Honma\nfrom third to move the Trojans to 17-0 on the season. USC's 17-game winning streak is the second longest in program history, trailing only the 1955 team's 19-game winning streak. San Diego falls to 7-9 with the loss.\nThe Trojans took a 5-3 lead into the seventh, but San Diego came up with three runs in the top of the inning to grab a 6-5 advantage.\nWill Stickney\ntied the game with a pinch-hit RBI single in the bottom of the seventh to even it up for USC.\nThe Trojans had the bases loaded with no outs in the ninth, but were unable to push across a run to end the game in regulation. USC again loaded the bases in the 10\nth\n, and this time Lopez came through, plating Honma on a medium depth fly ball to center.\nEight USC pitchers took the mound in the game, with\nAdam Troy\npicking up the victory after tossing a scoreless top of the 10\nth\n.\nBen Cushnie\nworked scoreless eighth and ninth innings for the Trojans in his season debut.\nAce Whitehead\nalso had a scoreless outing, getting the start and tossing 2.0 innings in his USC debut.\nThe Toreros scored twice in the fourth inning to take a 2-1 lead, but for the second game in a row,\nAndrew Lamb\nsparked the offense with a three-run homer in the bottom half of the inning. It was Lamb's third homer of the year.\nThe visitors cut it back to a one-run game in the fifth, loading the bases and scoring on a wild pitch, but\nPaul Grossman\ngot out of the inning with a flyout to center.\nAugie Lopez\ndoubled off the wall in right to score\nJack Basseer\nin the bottom of the sixth to push it to a 5-3 USC lead.\nTOP PERFORMERS\nAndrew Lamb\n: 1-for-4, 3-R HR, BB\nMaximo Martinez\n: 3-for-5, RBI, R, BB, 2 2B\nAce Whitehead\n: 2.0 IP, 0H, 0R, 0BB, K\nBen Cushnie\n: 2.0 IP, H, 0R, 2BB\nCOMING UP\nUSC hits the road against Northwestern this weekend, with all three games broadcast on B1G+."
